ðŸš€ Basic Docker Commands
ðŸ‘‰ 1. Check Docker Version
docker --version
docker version


ðŸ‘‰ 2. Download an Image
Pull an image from Docker Hub:
docker pull ubuntu

3. List Images
docker images

4.Remove an image
docker rmi <image_id>

5. Run a Container
docker run <image_name>

Run in interactive terminal:
docker run -it ubuntu

Run in background:
docker run -d ubuntu

6. List Containers
docker ps

All containers:
docker ps -a

7. Stop a Container
docker stop <container_id>

8. Start a Container
docker start <container_id>

9. Remove a Container
docker rm <container_id>

10. Container Logs
docker logs <container_id>

11. Execute Command Inside Container
docker exec -it <container_id> bash

12. Build Image From Dockerfile
docker build -t myapp .

13. Copy Files
docker cp <container_id>:/path/in/container /path/in/host

14. View Container Details
docker inspect <container_id>

15. Prune Unused Data
docker system prune

